            'men.stat_card.1': '<div class="stat-number red" style="font-size:1.4rem;">1 of 4</div> <div class="stat-label">people will have a mental health problem this year</div>',
            'men.stat_card.2': '<div class="stat-number red" style="font-size:1.4rem;">970M</div> <div class="stat-label">people live with anxiety or depression (WHO, 2023)</div>',
            'men.stat_card.3': '<div class="stat-number" style="font-size:1.4rem;">80%</div> <div class="stat-label">of the cases are related to lifestyle — not biology</div>',
            'men.stat_card.4': '<div class="stat-number">20 min</div> <div class="stat-label">naturally reduces cortisol by up to 20%</div>',
            'men.stat_card.5': '<div class="stat-number">120 min</div> <div class="stat-label">per week in nature = significantly better mental health (BMJ, 2023)</div>',
            'men.stat_card.6': '<div class="stat-number red" style="font-size:1.1rem;">"I\'m very stressed"</div> <div class="stat-label">You say it as a matter of fact. Treat it as a symptom.</div>',
            'men.stat_card.7': '<div class="stat-number red" style="font-size:1.1rem;">"I can\'t do without coffee"</div> <div class="stat-label">A sign of chronic poor sleep. Coffee masks, not cures.</div>',
            'men.stat_card.8': '<div class="stat-number red" style="font-size:1.1rem;">"Everyone is anxious"</div> <div class="stat-label">Anxiety is an epidemic, not the norm. The epidemic is being treated.</div>',
            'men.stat_card.9': '<div class="stat-number red" style="font-size:1.1rem;">"I don\'t feel like doing anything"</div> <div class="stat-label">Anhedonia. It\'s not character—it\'s a symptom of an exhausted nervous system.</div>',
            'men.stat_card.10': '<div class="stat-number" style="font-size:1.2rem;">80/20</div> <div class="stat-label">80% good habits + 20% freedom = sustainable lifestyle</div>',
            'men.stat_card.11': '<div class="stat-number" style="font-size:1.2rem;">The direction</div> <div class="stat-label">is more important than perfection. Small steps in the right direction add up.</div>',
            'men.info_box.1': '<h3>Try</h3> <p style="margin-top:8px;">first Just do this today:<strong>30 minutes without phone</strong> and <strong>10 slow breaths</strong>. It doesn\'t solve everything, but it does reduce the noise enough to get some control back.</p>',
            'men.info_box.2': '<h3 style="color:var(--purple);">The difference between "normal" and "common"</h3> <p style="margin-top:10px;">100 years ago type 2 diabetes was rare. He\'s "normal" now. Obesity is "normal". Anxiety is "normal". Chronic stress is "normal".</p> <p style="margin-top:8px;"><strong>Normal means biologically healthy. Common means widespread.</strong> These two things are not the same. Don\'t take "everyone has it" as a reason not to address it.</p>',
            'men.info_box.3': '<p>Everything on this page helps <strong>prevention and management.</strong> But if you have chronic depression, panic attacks, severe anxiety, an eating disorder, or thoughts of self-harm —<strong>good habits alone are not enough.</strong></p> <p style="margin-top:10px;">Psychotherapy (especially CBT — Cognitive Behavioral Therapy) is <strong>scientifically proven method</strong> with measurable, lasting effect. Asking for help is a sign of strength, not weakness.</p>',
            'men.info_box.4': '<p>This page contains a lot of information. It can seem like a long list of "shoulds". It\'s not.</p> <p style="margin-top:10px;"><strong>No one meditates, exercises, sleeps 8 hours, doesn\'t scroll, doesn\'t drink alcohol, and writes a journal every day.</strong> No one. And you shouldn\'t.</p> <p style="margin-top:10px;">The goal is not perfection—the goal is direction. If you do 3 of these things regularly, you are already ahead of 80% of people. If you sometimes scroll until 2 in the morning, drink more than planned or spend all day on the couch —<strong>don\'t punish yourself. Admit it, smile, and move on.</strong></p> <p style="margin-top:10px; color:var(--muted);">However, it is important to know that <strong>everything has consequences.</strong> Chronic stress, insomnia, isolation, and overconsumption don\'t go away just because we normalize them. Knowledge is not guilt—it is choice.<em>You choose how much of these things you do and when.</em></p>',
            'men.cta_section.1': '<h2>Mind and body are one.<br/><em class="purple">Take care of both.</em></h2> <p style="color:#888; max-width:480px; margin:0 auto 24px;">Check out the 7-day plan that covers both—nutrition, exercise, and mental health.</p> <a class="btn btn-purple" href="start.html">See the 7-day plan →</a> ',
            'men.purple.1': 'everything',
